h1. Windows

Thanks to Mauricio Troviano, we have an installer for Windows.

The installer contains the necessary Qt dlls, is able to download and install Python 
and provides a binary version of PyQt that works with SciDAVis. The manual is not included due to its
size and our intention to update it in between releases. Likewise, translations currently have to be
installed seperately. Future releases of the installer may be extended to handle these things.

That said, all necessary links and files can be found
"here":http://sourceforge.net/project/platformdownload.php?group_id=199120&sel_platform=7767.

